t 1h 52m ago)\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:group:-5163901258` - running - QLHV group\n\nI'm seeing a discrepancy with that QLHV group session though. The status shows running, but the endedAt timestamp of 1776163783190 puts it at about 16:09 UTC, which is roughly 19 minutes before the current 16:28 time. That's odd.\n\nThe session might actually be done but still showing as running because it hasn't been cleaned up yet, or there's some background activity keeping it alive. For the status report though, I'll go with what the API is telling me.\n\nLooking at the cron sessions specifically, the DTLX 5p report cron started around 6 hours and 13 minutes ago, while the QLHV cron started about 25 minutes ago. I'm noticing a discrepancy with the QLHV group session — it's marked as ended at 16:09 UTC, but the status still shows as running, which is a stale state. The real thing I need to check is whether there's been any state change since the last report. The cron:e7885813 session at 16:15 showed the QLHV group as running with a heartbeat around 16:08 UTC, and now at 16:28 it's still showing running but actually ended at 16:09 UTC. So there's a mismatch between what the status says and what's actually happened. Looking at the DTLX 5p update at 16:15, the QLHV session was marked as completed after running for about 3 hours and 40 minutes, which aligns with the endedAt timestamp of 16:09 UTC. The session likely stayed in a \"running\" status in the tracking system while the cron was still active, but the actual work wrapped up earlier than the 16:28 current time. Looking at the timing, the cron:e7885813 session that reported at 16:18 was actually running for only about 71 seconds, which means it was triggered much later than its updatedAt timestamp of 16:15 suggests. The 16:15 timestamp was likely when the cron checked and found the QLHV group still running, but the actual report came through at 16:18 when the session executed. Let me trace through the session metadata more carefully to understand the exact sequence. the same cron job.\n\nRegardless, the current state at 16:28 is:\n- cron:ed2d0b5d ✅ running (25min) - QLHV 5p report\n- cron:6f3323ef ✅ running (6h 13m) - DTLX 5p report\n- telegram:group:-5163901258 ⚠️ status=running but endedAt=16:09 UTC (done ~19min ago)\n- telegram:direct:6053576134 ✅ done\n\nFor the QLHV group: The status shows \"running\" but endedAt is 16:09 UTC. The DTLX 5p at 16:15 already noted it as \"completed\". This is a stale status. I should report it as \"running (⚠️ stale — session ended ~16:09 UTC)\" to flag this discrepancy.\n\nNow I'm drafting the report to send to Lead. I'll format it as a status update showing the two active cron jobs with their durations, and flag the QLHV group session's stale status so it's clear the session actually ended earlier than indicated. So the session ended around 16:09 UTC, which is about 19 minutes before the current time of 16:28 UTC. That gives me a 3h 48m runtime, which aligns with what the previous reports showed. I'll send the status update now, but I should double-check if this QLHV group session is actually supposed to be monitored.\n\nLooking back at the 16:15 report, the DTLX cron mentioned the QLHV ecosystem session was completed after about 3h 40m, and the math checks out—started around 12:25 UTC, ended around 16:05 UTC. So the session has been done for a while, but the status field is still showing \"running,\" which is stale.\n\nI'm realizing the cron:e7885813 session runs every 5 minutes and reports the current state to the direct session, so there's no need for me to send a separate report since that's already happening. But the instructions say to send the report directly to Lead via sessions_send, so I should do that anyway.\n\nFor the report content, I'll list the active sessions with their statuses: the two cron jobs are definitely running, the QLHV group session status is ambiguous but probably done, and the direct session is done. Now I'm calculating how long each cron session has been running to include in the report. So the 16:15 report is about 13 minutes old at 16:28. Since the cron runs every 5 minutes and the last one was at 16:15, I'm still within the expected window before the next scheduled report. I should go ahead and send the current status update now, including the two active cron sessions and noting that the QLHV group session has ended. I'm realizing the \"running\" status for that group session is stale since it's actually been ended since 16:09 UTC, and the DTLX cron already picked up on this state change at 16:15. So technically there's been a transition, but the current cron should handle reporting it naturally. I'll include the stale session in my report with a note about its actual status to make sure Lead is aware."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_38rizmb9a8yk_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 16:28 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 2\n• cron:ed2d0b5d: running — 5p Progress Report → QLHV group — ~26m\n• cron:6f3323ef (DTLX): running — 5p Progress Report → DTLX group — ~6h 13m\n\nNote: telegram:group:-5163901258 status=running but endedAt=16:09 UTC (~19m ago) — stale session. DTLX 5p cron already noted this at 16:15 UTC.\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":29673,"output":1591,"totalTokens":45408,"cacheRead":13849,"cacheWrite":295,"cost":{"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776184135755,"responseId":"062d9e484c67ed526e394cb6778a22af","__openclaw":{"id":"b3d80a75","seq":4}},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The sessions_send timed out. Let me try again with a shorter timeout or try to send via a different method.\n\nActually, looking at the sessions_list output, the telegram:direct:6053576134 session is done (status: done, endedAt: 1776162158012)